This came out of a [discussion with a customer on CAC|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Working+with+Blueprints?focusedCommentId=346947791#comment-346947791].

The Content Report Table Macro displays the 'Creator' of reported pages and their last modified date.

We should supply parameters (checkboxes) for the Page Properties Report macro to do the same. 

h3. Workaround
Use [User Macros|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Writing+User+Macros] to create these fields and add them to the Page Properties macro.

# Create a custom [user macro|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Writing+User+Macros] that calls the last modified date and a macro that calls the creator name.
# Use the following macros:
{code:title=Creator Name}
$content.getCreatorName()
{code}
{code:title=Modified Date}
$action.dateFormatter.formatDateTime($content.getLastModificationDate())
{code}
# Place these macros into the Page Properties macro fields
# The report will now show these values

Steps to reproduce:

1) Change the Confluence layout to 2 columns;
2) Create some text and just below create code blocks;
3) Copy some preformatted content (from word for instance) and paste it into the code blocks;
4) See that the first line of the code block is changed  from "Preformatted" to "Paragraph."
5) So all then content has to be reselected so it will be selected as preformatted again.
6) When doing this the text either disappears completely, or shifts way down the page out of the code block "box" in edit mode.

